Do you also love crafting and decorating? Then you‚Äôve come to the right place. Today I show you some brilliant DIY crafts you can try at home. Let‚Äôs start with 3D pens. Those little powerful handheld tools will help you add some flare to your next big project or fix something broken. 

For example, using a watermelon halve, you can create a hat. 

Have you ever broken your favorite coffee mug? Then, instead of chucking it away, use your 3D pen to fix it. Just make sure you fill the area with multiple coarse layers that go in different directions to ensure no liquid will seep through.  

If you‚Äôre looking for more challenging projects. I show you how to turn a steel drum into a fully functional BBQ grill. You can also take an old chair from the trash and restore it into beautiful furniture. Or, take a soda can, an old helicopter toy, and re-design it from scratch.

snippet.description:

Episode 555: Jethalal Intoxicated With Bhaang
-----------------------------------------
Taarak is stressed as Jethalal is intoxicated and tries to confess his love for Babita. Taarak decides to lock him up in his house and leave for shiv yatra. Daya decides to stay back till Jethalal comes.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
-------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble for all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalaal.

Episode 556: Everyone Looks For Jethalal
-----------------------------------------
Everyone assumes Jethalal to be kidnapped as he's gone for a long time. Taarak asks the doctor about how to minimize the effect of Bhaang. Jethalal realized how he consumed sweets which turned out to be intoxicated.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
-------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble for all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalaal.

snippet.title: Writer Fighter Hua - Sit-down Comedy by Varun Grover
snippet.description:
Wrote and performed this standup bit for the first edition of SWA Awards 2020 organised by the official body that represents all the lyricists and writers of Indian film industry - The Screenwriters Association. 

First standup video shot completely at home since this lockdown began. Bada mushkil hai ghar pe comedy karna. Aadmi bewakoof lagta hai hawa mein joke sunaate huye. But maybe ab yahi future hai. I mean 'bewakoof lagna.' 

Shot by: Raj Kumari 
Edited by: Abhishek Bhutwani 
Sound by: Sreejith Menon 
Created for: Screenwriters Association (SWA) 
Title inspired by: Jaspal Bhatti's Flop Show's title song

snippet.title: ITS A.... !?! ARE WE HAVING A BOY OR A GIRL?!?

Hey guys! Today we are finding out what we are having (eeeek!) we filmed this 10 weeks ago, and just wanted to keep it to ourselves for a while before we shared with the world. We're having a....?!!!! 

The disbelief is more or less that in this entire 2 day span with having the 20 week ultrasound, and getting the results of the baby, that it really made real the reality of being parents. We KNEW it was real, but we hadn't seen the baby since 8 weeks, so this (being we saw the baby, how much the baby had grown etc) and the NEXT DAY found out what we were having, that is my shock and disbelief. How real it all is, and just picturing what our life will be like from here on out. We are SO EXCITED and cannot handle it!! bursting with love

snippet.title: ASMR You're in Among Us
snippet.description:
Use code GIBI for 30% off your purchase at https://www.GFUEL.com !!! Did anyone catch the stream yesterday!?!?!

I got to play Among Us with such a wild crew I actually am still recovering LOL. If you want to watch the vod, the crew was Pewdiepie, MoistCritikal, Summit1g, dakotaz, Logic, xQc, adept., Trainwrecktv, and Lirik! NOT ASMR lmao - https://www.twitch.tv/videos/751722045

So this all coincided SUPER well, I was already planning on making an Among Us video after our ASMR stream (https://www.twitch.tv/videos/742050877) and here we are! I hope you enjoy! You'll probably pick it up pretty quick, but you are the secret second impostor GAINING MY TRUST while I do tasks! Good luck.....

snippet.title: Israel Adesanya's Chest & His PERFECT Leg Kicks! Doctor Reacts to UFC 253
snippet.description:
Thanks to fuboTV for sponsoring this video! 
Go to http://fubotv.com/brianmd to start your FREE trial and get 15% off your first month.

Israel Adesanya defeated Paulo Costa at UFC 253 to retain the middleweight championship belt and he did it in part thanks to nearly perfect lower leg kicks. But also, what's the deal with his chest looking so strange during the fight? In this video we'll review why Adesanya's leg kicks were so effective in beating Costa, plus, what could possibly be going on with the MMA star's chest? 

UPDATE: I was off on the point about unilateral vs bilateral as many have pointed out in the comments. I appreciate the feedback and everyone pointing this out and will always admit if I missed something. In this case i was quick to defend an athlete I saw being accused unfairly of steroid use and didnt do enough research on a topic outside of my expertise. lesson learned, will keep working to be better.

snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS | Liverpool vs Arsenal (3-1) | Premier League
snippet.description:
Our winning start to the season is over after Liverpool fought back to beat us at Anfield.
 
A bizarre goal from Alex Lacazette saw us lead the champions and lay the foundations for a memorable result. But our advantage lasted just two minutes as Sadio Mane and Andy Robertson struck to turn the tide in Liverpool's favour.

Diogo Jota then put the game to bed moments before full time with a crisp finish into the bottom left-hand corner.

snippet.title: BTS: Tiny Desk (Home) Concert
snippet.description:
For new music, the latest Tiny Desk (home) concerts and more, sign up for the NPR Music newsletter, sent weekly: npr.org/nprmusicnewsletter

Sept. 21, 2020 | Stephen Thompson -- We've been trying to make a BTS Tiny Desk concert happen for years now ‚Äî even gaming out ways we might move Bob Boilen's desk far enough forward to accommodate the superstar Korean boy band's dance moves.

In the end, it took a global pandemic ‚Äî and the launch of Tiny Desk (home) concerts back in March ‚Äî to make something happen. With BTS cooped up in Seoul, the group held true to the series's spirit by convening a live band for its Tiny Desk debut, and even arranged to perform in a workspace with a music-friendly backdrop: the record store VINYL & PLASTIC by Hyundai Card in BTS's hometown.

Opening with this summer's inescapable "Dynamite" ‚Äî the group's first single to hit No. 1 in the U.S., as well as its first song to be fully recorded in English ‚Äî BTS leaned hard into the new track's celebratory, "Uptown Funk"-adjacent vibes. From there, the group dipped into its back catalog, seizing on the opportunity to showcase its quieter side while (mostly) staying uncharacteristically seated. The breezily propulsive "Save ME," from 2016, ultimately gave way to a full-on power ballad in 2017's reflective "Spring Day."

The latter track seemed especially true to BTS's hopeful nature: Introduced with a few optimistic words from rapper and singer RM ("It's been the roughest summer ever, but we know that spring will come"), the song reflects on a need to wait out hard times, even as the weight of present-day pain feels oppressive.

BTS had intended to spend 2020 delighting the BTS Army in arenas around the world, only to spend these last few months performing in isolation. Released on the last day of a grim season, "Spring Day" provides a nice reminder of what awaits us on the other side. We just have to get through fall and winter first.

SET LIST
"Dynamite"
"Save ME"
"Spring Day"

MUSICIANS
V: vocals; Jin: vocals; Jimin: vocals; J-Hope: vocals; RM: vocals; SUGA: vocals; Jungkook: vocals; KHAN: drums; DOCSKIM: keyboard; Kim Kiwook: bass; Shyun: guitar

CREDITS
Video and Audio by: Big Hit Entertainment; Producer: Stephen Thompson; Audio Mastering Engineer: Josh Rogosin; Video Producer: Morgan Noelle Smith; Associate Producer: Bobby Carter; Executive Producer: Lauren Onkey; Senior VP, Programming: Anya Grundmann


ABOUT THE SERIES

The Tiny Desk is working from home for the foreseeable future. Introducing NPR Music's Tiny Desk (home) concerts, bringing you performances from across the country and the world. It's the same spirit ‚Äî stripped-down sets, an intimate setting ‚Äî just a different space.

snippet.description:
Everton made it three wins from three in the Premier League - and five from five in all competitions - to continue their perfect start to 2020/21 with a 2-1 victory at Crystal Palace. snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS | WOLVES 1-3 MAN CITY | De Bruyne, Foden, Jim√©nez, Jesus
snippet.description:
Goals from Kevin De Bruyne and Phil Foden put a dominant City two goals up at the break.

But Wolves rallied after half-time and City had to weather a ferocious storm, especially for the first 20 minutes or so, before Gabriel Jesus wrapped up the points with the last kick of the game.

snippet.description:
Israel Adesanya and Paulo Costa spent months trading verbal shots, but when it came time to step into the Octagon at UFC 253, the only meaningful blows that landed were those of middleweight champion. After spending a full round beating up Costa's lead leg, Adesanya finished the challenger with punches in the second round of the main event on Fight Island in Abu Dhabi.

snippet.title: Americans have rejected 'horrific' treatment of Coney Barrett
snippet.description:
The Democrats and the Left in the US will look to ‚Äúabsolutely destroy‚Äù President Donald Trump‚Äôs Supreme Court nominee Amy Coney Barrett in the exact same way they destroyed Brett Kavanaugh, according to Sky News host James Morrow.

President Trump announced Justice Barrett as his nominee to replace deceased former associate justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg after she passed away two weeks ago after a long battle with cancer.

The President noted the passing of Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg, describing the former Judge as a ‚Äútrue American legend‚Äù and a ‚Äúlegal giant‚Äù.

Mr Trump went on to introduce Ms Barrett saying, ‚Äútoday it is my honour to nominate one of our nation‚Äôs most brilliant and gifted legal minds to the supreme court‚Äù.

However, people have begun to ramp up the hate rhetoric against Trump‚Äôs nominee, specifically focussing on her conservative views, and her family.

Justice Barrett has seven children, two of which were adopted from Haiti sparking some to label her and her husband ‚Äúwhite colonisers‚Äù.

Mr Morrow said the Democrats will ‚Äúnot be able to resist over playing their hand‚Äù which will drive middle America into the president‚Äôs hands.

‚ÄúThis should be the absolute American Dream. It‚Äôs everything that they (the Left) hate, this lovely happy successful interracial family,‚Äù he said.

‚ÄúThey are going to try and destroy this woman and middle America is going to look at it and say ‚Äòguys what is your problem‚Äô‚Äù.

Sky News host Rowan Dean said it is going to be a ‚ÄúTrump landslide because the average American looks at this stuff and thinks it‚Äôs horrific‚Äù.
